name: Test -> Battery,
description: Use a voltimeter to test the battery energy content, outcome='NOMINAL\n\nFeedback:\n- The battery voltage was successfully measured at 12.0 V on the positive terminal relative to ground and 0.0 V on the negative terminal. This is consistent with an adequately charged battery and does **not** indicate a \'BatteryDepleted\' problem.\n- Note: There was an additional note stating: "[The simulation did not converge — the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state.]" However, this does not appear to impact the voltage reading at the battery at this step, though it may suggest other circuit issues outside the battery itself.\n\nRecommendation:\n- Based on the readings, the battery appears to be nominal and not depleted.\n- If system instability persists, further investigation elsewhere in the circuit is suggested.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Adjust -> MainLoad,
description: Make sure the lamp is properly installed in its holder, outcome='ANOMALOUS\n\nFeedback:\nThe lamp ("Main Load (lamp)") is visually observed and is currently lit, which would typically suggest nominal operation. However, the simulation failed to converge due to the circuit being described as unstable or oscillating. This instability is an indication of an anomalous circuit condition, which may be related to improper installation or some other underlying issue affecting the holder or connections. Please further inspect the lamp\'s seating, contacts, and check for electrical stability before proceeding.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=10.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
